Commentary.Commentary: 24 overs left in the day. How many wickets can Australia snare? Can the Kiwis see off the day without any damage? The players are back out in the middle. Tom Latham and Tom Blundell will open up for the Black Caps. Mitchell Starc will start off proceedings to Latham. Here we go!

Coming to the Kiwi bowling, did Kane Williamson call it wrongly at the toss? Or did his bowlers not use the conditions to the best of their ability? Or did Australia just simply play well? One would guess the third option. Looking at the 10 mm grass on the pitch, it would have been a no-brainer to field. The Kiwis bowled well throughout on Day 1 but they were kept at bay. It was only on Day 2 that their bowling let them down. Australia played traditional Test cricket, seeing off the new ball, batting patiently and scoring off the bad balls. Neil Wagner was the bowler who bowled with venom, even when things were not going for him or his team. He got 4 wickets with the best of those being the brute to Steven Smith and ironically, with one wicket left in the innings, it was Wagner who took the catch to have Australia bowled out.

Travis Head says that it is always good to contribute to what has been a good couple of days for Australia and hopes they can continue to do well. Further adds he has been playing well and he is happy to convert the start he got on Boxing Day into a big one.

For once, the headlines will not have a Steven Smith or a Marnus Labuschagne. Travis Head and Tim Paine will hog it. How well did the skipper play? His 72-ball half century is his quickest in Tests, which asserted that he was out there to counter-attack and not bow down. That lifted Head up as he went on to score a century and held the innings together. Here he is, talking to Kat Loughnan.

When Trent Boult dismissed Joe Burns with a ripper of an inswinger on the 4th ball of a match, little did we expect that Australia would cross 100 4 times. But this is exactly the type of scorecard that any batting skipper would want. 5 consecutive 50-plus run stands from 1/1, with the last one reading 150. Yes, Steven Smith and Marnus Labuschagne scored but for a change, they were not the only ones. Warner played a very good hand in seeing off the new ball in testing conditions while Matthew Wade did well to ensure that there was no collapse after the Labuschagne dismissal.
So nothing much post the Tea break for Australia. 36/5 in 8.1 overs. Ouch. In a normal scenario. It's okay. In this scenario. To make an overall summary, a phenomenal batting display by the hosts.

OUT! Wagner takes the catch! No fifer for him but AUSTRALIA HAVE BEEN BOWLED OUT FOR 467! A short one on middle, Lyon pulls it nicely, but it does not have the power behind it to clear the long boundaries here. It goes towards fine leg where Wagner takes a good catch.
Misfield and two! A slower one, fuller outside off, Pattinson strokes it towards cover where the fielder does not stop it. Two taken.
A short one on middle, Pattinson ducks under it.
On the pads, it is flicked through square leg for one.
On the fuller side on off, Lyon strokes it to covers.
A full toss on middle, Pattinson works it through mid-wicket for one.
A yorker on middle, Pattinson does well to jam it out.
On the stumps, NL plays it towards mid on.
Back of a length and on off, Lyon keeps it out.
On off, Lyon blocks it nicely.
Nathan Lyon is the last man in.

OUT! Taken! Cummins bags a duck! Another batter dismissed off a full toss. Southee bowls a slower one, it is a low full toss. Cummins is a touch early in the flick and hence, it goes uppishly towards mid-wicket. Latham there times his jump and takes a good catch with both his hand stretched upwards.
Southee lands this on a length and outside off, Pattinson plays it late through point for one.
FOUR! Up and over! Tim Southee has now gone for 100 runs. A short one on middle, Pattinson pulls it over mid-wicket. No one in the deep so a boundary results.
A full toss on middle, it is worked towards mid-wicket. A wicket maiden for Wagner.
A short one now, Cummins looks to play the upper cut but does not connect.

Confusion but safe! On a length and around off, Cummins strokes it towards Williamson at covers. He misfields. Cummins wants a run but is sent back. Rightly so as had they gone for it, it would have been very risky.
On the fuller side, Cummins strokes it to covers.

OUT! CAUGHT! Wagner gets his fourth. However, the first thing he does is after picking a wicket is walks upto Head and shakes his hand. Now all the Kiwi players do so. Head walks off to a standing ovation from the crowd. End of an excellent innings from him. He too falls in the attempt to score some quick runs. He makes room again and Wagner bowls a full toss. He looks to go big but ends up splicing it towards cover where Santner takes an easy catch. Australia though continue to bat on.
A yorker on the stumps, Head squeezes it out towards point.
Another short one, Head pulls it hard but very close to the fielder at mid-wicket. A single taken.
On the shorter side, closer to the body of Head. He looks to upper cut it but misses.
Fuller and on off, this is hit down to long off for one.
A muted appeal! This is angled into the batter. Pattinson keeps it out with his bat and pad close to each other. Southee appeals as he feels it is pad first but nothing from the umpire.
On the shorter side outside off, Head cuts it behind point. The fielder in the deep runs to his right and makes a diving stop. Only the one taken.
On the pads, it is worked towards fine leg for one.
FOUR! Crunched! Back-to-back boundaries! Head clears his front leg and this is bowled full and on middle, it is hammered through covers for another boundary. 10 from the over.
FOUR! Nicely played! A short one and on off, Head plays the upper cut. It goes very fine on the off side for a boundary. 450 up for Australia.
A bouncer, right at the head of Travis, he just about ducks in time.
Full on middle, driven straight to mid on.
A lovely follow-up. Head backs away to the leg side and Wagner follows him with a yorker on leg stump. Head just about gets his bat down on time to push it towards mid on.

NOT OUT! Umpire's call it is! That was very close. It could have gone either way to be honest. Wagner runs in and lands it on middle, Head shuffles right across and looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards fine leg as the batters run two. The bowler in the meantime makes a huge appeal but it is turned down. After a discussion, the Kiwi players review. Replays roll in and it shows the ball to be clipping the top of middle and leg. New Zealand do not lose their review. The umpire after everything signals leg byes.
Review time! A huge shout for an LBW has been turned down. New Zealand review. Head is the man in question. Looks close.
FOUR! Lovely shot to get off the mark! It is just behind a driving length around off, Pattinson creams it through covers. Latham gives it a chase and also puts in a dive but his effort goes in vain.
Full and wide outside off, Pattinson goes after it but misses.
Back of a length and on off, Head guides it towards point for one.

FOUR! 100 for Travis Head! Takes his helmet off and raises both his hands one holding the helmet and the other the bat. The crowd is up on its feet and so are his teammates applauding the knock. It is his second in this format. A very patient innings by him. He gets a gift to get there. Full and wide outside off, Head squeezes it through point and bags a boundary. We will now probably see him change gears here.
Full and very wide outside off, left alone.
James Pattinson is the new man in.

OUT! In the air... taken! Starc fails to make an impact. He was sent to score some quick runs but falls in the attempt to do so. Southee bowls a slower one, it is fuller in length. Starc looks to go over mid off but fails to get the correct connection. Williamson takes an easy catch. Two wickets in two overs for the Kiwis.
Tim Southee is back now!
Misses out again! Full and around middle, flicked straight to square leg. Head stays on 99.
Full and outside off, stays low, Travis looks to punch but ends up chopping it on the bounce towards first slip. The fielder dives to his left to stop.
Whoa! That is a good surprised ball. Wagner bowls a high full toss, which dips on its way towards the batsman. But Travis is watchful, sees the ball till the last moment and defends.
There is the single. The crowd applauds, not for Starc getting off the mark but because Head gets back on strike. Full and down the leg side, tickled towards fine leg for a single.
Full and down the leg side, left alone.
Mitchell Starc comes in at number 8, replacing his skipper.

OUT! LBW! Wicket for Wagner but everyone looks surprised. That review seemed to be more out of desperation but it has struck gold. A length ball, outside off, Paine gets across to work it to the leg side but misses and is hit on the pads. Wagner appeals instantly but umpire Marais Erasmus does not react. Now, here is the interesting thing about the review. The men behind the stumps are not too keen about the referral but Wagner wants it. Williamson agrees and signals the 'T'. To the naked eye, the impact looks outside off and given that Paine has been hit on the knee roll, the height seems to be an issue as well. But here comes Ball Tracker. The impact is in line and the projection is shown to be hitting the stumps! Even Marais Erasmus is surprised by that. But Paine has to go after a wonderful knock. The 150-run stand has been broken at last.
An LBW review against Tim Paine! To the naked eye, it seemed like the impact was outside off. Here comes Ball Tracker. Goodness me, impact in line and ball hitting the stumps! What a review!
Neil Wagner to partner Mitchell Santner. A real workhorse. 34-10-70-2 so far.
Full and outside off pushed towards cover for a quick single.
Turn and bounce there. Outside off, Tim initially looks to leave but then attempts to cut. Is beaten.
Outside off, Paine drives it towards long off but Santner dives to his left to stop.
Full on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on but short mid-wicket intercepts.
Moves to 99. Full and outside off, head presses this with soft hands towards cover and sets off for a run.
Full on middle, pushed through mid on for a single.

We are into the final session of Friday. 33 overs left. How long will Australia bat? 10 overs? 15 overs? Out come Travis Head and Tim Paine. The former is on 98 while the skipper will be on strike. Mitchell Santner to start off proceedings. Here we go...
... DAY 2, SESSION 3 ...

Nothing much is happening off the deck. Expect the Aussies to come out all guns blazing post Tea with a 'nothing-much-to-lose' attitude. They may potentially look at playing till Drinks, get as close to 500 as possible and then declare. That could well pave way for some cheap wickets for the Kiwis. Join us back at 3.30 pm local (0430 GMT). 33 overs left in the day.

Is the match gone out of bounds for New Zealand? Well, if India, England or South Africa might have been batting next, they might have even covered the deficit up, with some fast scoring. But the Black Caps, barring Ross Taylor and Colin de Grandhomme, are not known for scoring briskly. So, assuming our calculations are correct, it is going to be close to 2 days before they even get to Australia's score, let alone surpass it. But if they manage to do that, they can at least save the match.

The counter-attack continued from Head and Paine post Lunch and though the Kiwis tried to curtail the run rate, the partnership kept growing at a steady rate of 3.5. Both the batsmen have looked unperturbed and nothing much has troubled them off the pitch either.

A session which has probably ensured that the match and series will not go away from Australia. 95 runs in 30 overs, without losing a wicket. The hosts will be very, very happy and aiming for a declaration post Tea now.
Boo!!!!!! goes the crowd. the break. Full and around off, Head just pushes it towards point. TEA ON DAY 2!
Excellent work by Tom Latham! Full on off, Heads works it towards long on. Or, tries to. But cannot get past Tom Latham who dives to his right from short mid-wicket to stop it!
Full on middle, Head gets across and works it towards short mid-wicket.
Landed outside off, Travis dabs it towards gully where the fielder leaps to stop.

Ohhhh....opportunity missed. Boult gives a length ball on the pads and Travis Head has the full leg side part of the ground for his century. But he works it to the only man in front of square on the leg side - short mid-wicket!
A length ball around middle, moving away, Head pokes it towards gully.
Short and outside off, punched through the covers for a run. Moves to 98. Got an over now, to try and get that century before Tea.
A touch short, TH gets across and nudges it to the leg side.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Short and outside off Travis looks to cut but gets a bottom edge towards point.

Good awareness from Tim Paine. He sees that the Kiwis are a bit deep for him, as opposed to when Travis Head is on strike. Just works it through square leg, looks at Head and calls him through for a run.
Full on middle, Head comes down the track and pushes it towards long on for a single. Moves to 97.

FOUR LEG BYES! Boult gets swing but loses his radar. Full in length, but down the leg side. Paine misses his flick but the ball goes off his pads, well wide of the diving Watling, to the fine leg fence.
Outside off, dabbed straight to gully.
WIDE! That is short but a bit too high. It is generated at good pace too, but Paine just watches it sail past, over his head. The stand is worth 140 now.
Around middle, angling in, turned towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Full and outside off, swinging in, driven straight to short extra cover.
On a length, around off, Head hops and pushes it towards mid on.
Full and fast swinging in, worked towards short mid-wicket.
On middle, defended.
Slower through the air but shorter in length. Head slaps it through covers for one.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On off, TH goes back and keeps it out.
The arm ball outside off, Head looks to defend but does so inside the line, it goes off the outer half through short third man for two.
Very full and on off, this is squeezed out towards cover for one.
One more quick bumper, it gets Head hopping as he looks to fend it. The ball hits the higher part of the bat and lands on the off side. A good over comes to an end by Boult.
Boult looks to follow the bumper with a yorker but ends up bowling a low full toss which Head dugs out towards mid on.
Good ball and well played! A quick short ball and it is keeps rising. Head does well to hop and lower his arms to let it go.
Close! On a length and around off, this is tapped towards the point fielder and the batters take off. Nicholls gets to the ball, picks it up and has a shy at the striker's end but misses.
Outside off, let alone.
Angled into the pads, it is worked to mid on.

Fired on the pads, Head looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. There is an appeal from the bowler but the umpire shakes his head. Ball Tracker shows it would have clipped the leg pole. So it was a lot closer than we thought.
It is hit through covers for a single.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On the shorter side outside off, Head slaps it through covers for one.
On middle, this is eased down to long on for one.
Flatter and on middle, it is defended back to the bowler.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Head looks to cut but that shot is not on. He ends up chopping it on the off side. TH wanted a run but is sent back.
Another delivery on the stumps, kept out.
On off, defended.
On the shorter side, this is pulled on the leg side for one.

Lovely shot down the ground! It deserved a boundary but the batters get two. Fuller and around off, Paine shows the full face of the bat and hits it through mid off. Williamson from that position tracks it down and saves two for his side.
Back of a length and on off, blocked.
Trent Boult is back! 27-2-85-1 so far.
On middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Flatter and on off, TH keeps it out.
On off, blocked.
Quicker and just outside off, Head looks to cut but ends up chopping it on the off side.
Loopy ball on off, Santner pushes it towards cover for one.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
FOUR LEG BYES! A little too straight and slightly shorter. Head looks to flick but misses. It hits the pads and rolls down to the fine leg fence.
On the bounce! One more short one, Paine takes on the challenge of pulling. He does not get on top of the bounce completely. It goes uppishly but well short of fine leg. One taken.
Back of a length and on off, Paine pushes it to covers.
From around the wicket, he bangs it short, TP lets it go over him.
On the shorter side and on off, Paine keeps it out.
A short one on middle, Paine ducks under it.
Full and down the leg side, Paine flicks it through square leg. A run taken.
Comes down the track but then Santner drops it short. Travis adjusts quickly, goes back and dabs it towards point for a quick single. The stand is now worth 120.
Short and outside off, punched straight to short extra cover.
Outside off, turning away, short in length, punched through the covers for a single.
Full and outside off, driven straight to cover.
Full and around middle, flicked towards short mid-wicket.
Pushed to the cover region by the batsman. They pick up a single.
On the body, Paine looks to leave it but is hit on the body.
Paine comes down the track and Wagner bangs it short. Paine watches it go over him as he ducks under it. Strange from Paine there, not sure one would want to give Wagner the charge.
Another bouncer and another pull shot! To the man at short fine leg.
On the shorter side, Paine pulls it towards mid-wicket.
Bouncer! The batsman does well to evade it.
Outside off, not played at.
On middle, this is worked to the fielder at mid-wicket.
Gives it a lot of air and lands it on off, Paine strokes it through covers for one.
A single now as this is pushed towards cover. 400 up for the Aussies.
Another tossed up ball, it is played to the man at cover.
FOUR! Australia one short of 400 now! A full ball around off, Head loves it there, he creams it through covers for a boundary.
Shorter and on off, TH plays it towards cover and a single is taken.
Paine now plays a good pull shot through the leg side for one.
A short one down the leg side, Head helps it on its way down towards fine leg for one.
Slower one and on off, kept out.
A good bumper this one, Head ducks under it. Wide signaled but it was a decent short ball.
A short one and on middle, Head hops and keeps it out.
On the shorter side and on the body, Head looks to flick but it hits the glove. Luckily for Head, it rolls towards short fine leg.
On off, Paine stays back and pushes it to covers.
Flatter and around off, it is guided through point for one.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg for a single.
On middle, defended nicely.
Fired on the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, it is pushed to covers.
Change of ends for Mitchell Santner. 12-1-57-0 so far.

DRINKS! Australia continue to strengthen their position in the game! They have managed to score quickly, Head is nearing his ton and Paine will start to think of getting one too. The stand between the two has crossed 100. It will be interesting to see how much more will the Aussies add. The story is the same for the Kiwis, they need wickets which they aren't getting at regular intervals. Will the hosts continue to dominate or will we see a change?
On the body of Head, he nudges it on the leg side.
A good bumper, Travis ducks under it.
Good running! On the pads this time, Head works it wide of the fielder at fine leg and takes two.
Down the leg side, Head looks to flick but misses.

FOUR! One bounce and over the rope! 100-run stand comes up. Finally the Australians manage to covert a parntership into something significant. Also, Head moves into the 80s now. A short one by Wagner outside off, Head upper cuts it for a boundary in the third man region.
On the shorter side, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Neil Wagner is brought back in! 30-10-58-2 are his figures so far.
Full and outside off, tempting Paine to drive, he walks into the shot but shoulders arms.
Full and straight, watchfully defended.
Full and outside off, Head leans and steers it through point for a run.
Full and straight, Tim gets across and dangerously flicks it across the line. Would have been plumb LBW had he missed. But he manages to get it wide of mid on for a single.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Outside off, punched off the back foot for a single.

FOUR! Full and down the leg side, Paine gets across and looks to paddle. He nearly misses it but the ball takes the under edge and goes past the keeper. Ross Taylor at first slip tries to get across but the ball beats him. Paine moves to 60.
Fractionally short outside off, played with an open bat-face towards backward point.
Full and down the leg side, flicked straight to short mid-wicket.
Similar ball, well blocked out.
Quick, on the stumps, Paine defends it solidly.
Full and outside off, driven through the covers for a single.
Outside off, not played at.
FOUR! Cracking shot! This was so pleasing to the eye! Yes, it is a alf volley but you still need to put it away. Paine leans into it and creams it through covers for a boundary.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Colin looks to shape it from the leg pole to the off pole, no swing and Paine works it to mid-wicket.
Outside off again, Paine does not fiddle with it.
An outswinger outside off, left alone.
A full toss now, this is eased down to long on for one.
Head comes down the track and looks to work it past the bowler from his left. Santner moves quickly and stops it.
Another floated delivery around off, Paine strokes it through covers for one.
Tosses it up on off, it is driven to covers.
The batsman has played it to the point region. One run added to the total.
Ohhh! Brave leave! This lands just outside off, it goes on with the arm. Head lets it go. That was risky. If it would have turned in, Head could have been in trouble.
Shorter in length and outside off, TH cuts it through point for one.
On the off pole, Head keeps it out.
Back of a length and on off, it is pushed back to the bowler.
Very full outside off, Head is guilty of going way too hard at it. He mistimes it towards mid off.
Good stop! Slightly fuller and on off, Travis strokes it on the up towards cover. The fielder dives to his right and stops it.
Loose stroke this! It is a length delivery outside off, Head pokes at it away from his body and gets beaten.
Paine looks to innovate. He brings out the reverse sweep but find the man at point.
Flatter and on off, Paine keeps it out with ease.
On middle, Paine lunges and keeps it out.

Inside edge! This lands outside off, Head looks to push it against the turn through the off side but the ball turns back in. It takes the inside edge and goes between his legs towards fine leg for one.
Flatter and on off, Head goes back and works it on the leg side.
Very full on middle, Head hits it towards mid-wicket.

Mitchell Santner is back on! 9-1-49-0 so far. Meaning, 8 of his overs have gone for runs. This is his 6th spell. Clearly, the captain is not happy with his bowling at all, which is why he is not getting long spells. Lacking self-confidence perhaps.
Good running! Fuller and on off, Travis strokes it towards mid off for a quick run.
Lovely delivery! This lands just outside off, now due to the around the wicket angle, Head looks to play at it. The ball straightens and beats the outside edge.
Slightly fuller and outside off, TH hits it nicely but to the man at covers.
Angles another delivery on the middle pole, blocked.
Good length and on off, defended.
On the fuller side, Head strokes it to covers.

FOUR! Superb batting! Excellent use of the field placement. Just before this ball, Southee got square leg up. He then dished in a short one. But Paine was ready. Swivelled on the back foot and pulled it all along the ground, exactly through that region where the man at deep square leg was on the previous ball! An important HALF CENTURY for the captain. A pretty decent strike rate as well.
Square leg comes up now.
Another bouncer, down the leg side, Tim initially thinks of ducking but looking at the line, does not bother.
A bouncer now, the captain ducks.
Outside off, tapped through point for a single.
A bouncer, on middle, Head ducks.
Landed outside off, played straight to backward point.

LEADING EDGE, SAFE! Full and around off, Paine looks to flick, on the walk, but the ball takes the leading edge. Luckily for him, it does not carry to Henry Nicholls at gully. Probably that shot on the walk saved him. A happening over.
Outside off, left alone.
Not in control of that one. Full and around off, Head looks to flick but gets a leading edge through the covers. A single taken.

Nearly a wicket. De Grandhomme had been bringing the balls back into Head in his previous spell. Hence perhaps, Travis thought about flirting with this one. But this one moves away and beats the outside edge as TH looks to steer it towards third man.
Full and around middle, pushed towards mid on.
A length ball, around leg stump, defended towards the leg side.

Pickle juice coming in for Tim Paine. Probably suffering from cramps. New Zealand meanwhile, are done with the Tom Blundell experiment. The very reliable Colin de Grandhomme comes back on. 25-5-58-2 so far.
On the stumps, Paine pushes it back to the bowler.
Back of a length and on off, TP keeps it out.
A short one outside off, Paine lets it go.
A couple now! He moves to 47. Shorter and outside off, Paine slaps it through covers, not right off the middle but hit well enough to get two.

TOP EDGE AND FOUR! A good short one this, it is outside off and also bounces at a good height. Paine looks to pull but fails to get on top of the bounce. A top edge is produced which lands very fine on the leg side and goes for a boundary in the fine leg region.
On the fuller side and around off, it is hit to mid on.
Head comes down the track, Blundell fires in a full toss. TH hits it towards mid on.
FOUR! Slapped! Short and width on offer, Head pounces on it as he slaps it hard through covers. Need not run for that.
On middle, defended.
A short ball and on the body, it is pulled towards deep square leg for one. 350 is up for the hosts.
Paine misses out there! A full toss on off, Paine hits it hard but to covers.
On the shorter side again, Head pulls it towards deep backward square leg for one.
Blundell seems to have missed his run-up! He pulls up at the very end.
Similar ball, well kept out.
Fuller from Southee, outside off, watchfully defended.
Nicely done. Another short ball, around middle, Tim gets into position to pull. But then realizes that he is getting cramped for room and lets it pass.
FOUR! BOOM! Paine continues to attack. Short and around off, the skipper swivels and pulls it all along the ground through square leg! Moves to 40 from 56 balls. His 5th boundary.
Around off, solidly defended.
Full and around off, driven straight to mid off.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Well bowled! Slows it up nicely and lands it outside off, Head watches it and lets it go.
Shorter in length and outside off, Head stays back and slaps it hard to the cover fielder.
This time punches it nicely but straight to the man at covers.
Quicker and around off, Head goes back and mistimes his punch on the off side.
Shorter in length and outside off, Paine cuts it through point for one.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it into the pads, this is worked towards square leg for one. Just the single from the over.
On the off pole, Paine keeps it out nicely.
On the fuller side again, Paine strokes it back to the bowler.
Another very full ball and on middle, Paine strokes it to the man at mid on.
On the fuller side on off, Paine strokes it to mid off.
Full and outside off, it is shaping away. Left alone.
Tim Southee to bowl from the other end. 26-6-69-0 so far.
On the stumps, defended. Blundell's first over in Tests goes for 6.
One more short ball, it is pulled through square leg for only one this time.
Loopy ball on off, it is hit through covers for one.
Finally gets it right and beats the bat! It lands on off, Head looks to defend but the ball turns away and whizzes past the outside edge.
FOUR! A freebie and Travis Head puts it away nicely! Short and on middle, Head goes back and pulls it behind square on the leg side for a boundary. Also, that brings up 1000 Test runs for Head.
Flatter and on middle, it is shorter in length. Head works it to short fine leg.

We are back for the afternoon session! Out come the Australian batters Time Paine and Travis Head to resume their innings. Tom Blundell to start proceedings for the visitors. The away side trying something different. Here we go...
... Day 2, Session 2 ...

Australia are slowly reaching a score from where they will believe they cannot lose. Another 60 runs and they will be in firm control of this Test. The pitch is starting to break up, so Nathan Lyon is gonna be a handful. New Zealand need to come out after Lunch and try and dismiss the Aussies quickly. Join us back at 1.10 pm local (0210 GMT).

Neil Wagner is down for a chat with Kath Loughnan. On having the wood over Smith, Wagner feels that Smith is a class player and he played really well. On the dismissal, Wagner says that he had been trying everything and is lucky that this one went to hand. Praises Nicholls for that wonderful catch. On his relentlessness, Neil says that he just tries his best.

To be honest, the Black Caps did not bowl all that well in this session. They tied the Aussies before Drinks and the pressure showed - Smith was gone after the break. But then, in came Paine and started to attack. Head joined in and all of a sudden, runs started to flow.

79/1 in 27 overs. 52 of those came in the last hour. Australia would be pretty much happy with that. New Zealand threatened to bounce back into the game with the wicket of Steven Smith but this unbeaten 52-run stand between Travis Head and Tim Paine, that too, in just 74 balls, has pushed the Kiwis back again.
A couple! Short again and on the pads, it is pulled fine on the leg side for two. An expensive over this. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2!

FOUR! Through the off side this time! Short and outside off, Paine is quickly onto the back foot. He cuts it and it races to the backward point fence. 5th consecutive fifty-run stand is up in this innings.
Flatter and on off, Tim keeps it out nicely.
Floats it up on off, Paine keeps it out.
Another shorter one and on the pads, it is hit through square leg, in the gap for two.
FOUR! Too short and put away! It sits up to be hit, Paine goes back and pulls it through mid-wicket and it races away to the fence.
Fuller in length, Paine strokes it past the diving short over fielder, then past the diving cover fielder but can't get it past mid off who moves to his left and keeps it down to one.
Good bowling! Lands it on the length once again, it is kept out nicely.
On a length and outside off, Paine shoulders arms to this one.
Shorter in length and outside off, Head cuts it through point, there is protection in the deep and a single is taken.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, Head pushes it to mid on.
Very full and on middle, Paine works it to mid-wicket.
Slightly shorter in length, Paine rocks back and guides it through cover-point. Two taken.
On off, Paine pushes it to mid off.
Flatter and just outside off, Paine makes a leave. There was extra bounce there and hence Watling too failed to collect it cleanly.
On the pads, Head works it through square leg and a single is taken.
Starts off with a low full toss so the spin is out of contention. It is played to mid on.
Mitchell Santner is into the attack now. First signs of spin today. There are quite a few cracks on the wicket, it will be interesting to see if he gets some purchase.
Good length again and outside off, Head guides it behind point and takes one.
On middle, it is worked towards mid-wicket for one.
Back of a length and on off, Paine stays back and keeps it out.
On the fuller side and on off, Travis strokes it through covers for one.
Outside off again, it is left alone.
On the shorter side and outside off, Head plays it late and behind point for two.
A quick run! On the off pole, Head drops it towards cover and a single is taken.
Another one on off, TH works it to mid on.
Back of a length on off, Head pushes it to covers.
Another good effort in the field! Shorter and on middle, Paine pulls it over square leg. The fielder in the deep dives to his right and stops it. A single taken.
Ouch! Paine cops a blow! A short one and Paine fails to get away in time. It hits his shoulder. He shows no pain though.
A short one just outside off, Paine once again thinks of pulling it but he realizes again that it is a little too quick. He bails out again.
Outside off, not played at.
Outside off, not played at.

Nicely driven! Fifty for Head! 8th in Test matches. He has been short of runs and it is a much-needed half ton for him. He has a chance to score big here. He gets there with a fluent drive past the diving cover fielder for two.
Outside off, not played at.
Slashes and misses! This is shorter and outside off, there is some extra bounce. Head looks to cut but misses.
Good length and around off, Head stays back and keeps it out.
Another bumper to end! Paine sits under it.
One more bumper! Paine looks to leave it but is hit on the thigh pad.
EDGY FOUR! This is a length delivery around off, Paine opens the face and looks to run it down, the ball though goes off the outside edge and down to the third man fence.
On a length and around off, Tim Paine is solid in defense.
On the fuller side again, Paine strokes it to mid off.
Nice shot! Slightly fuller and around off, Head shows the full face of the bat and strokes it through mid off and takes three.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Outside off, not played at.
Length delivery and on off, Paine keeps it out nicely.
On the fuller side, Paine strokes it to mid off.
On the middle pole, Paine keeps it out nicely.
This starts outside off, it comes back in. Head pushes it towards point for one.
Colin de Grandhomme is on now!
Another bouncer! Paine may not have been expecting this one. He fails to get away in time. Luckily it just about misses his body.
Just about kisses the glove! A bumper down the leg side, Paine looks to pull but misses.
Nasty stuff! One more bumper, this is on the body of the batter. Paine looks to pull but then realizes it is a little too quick. Paine pulls out of the shot.
Bends his back on this one and it is a good short ball! Paine lets it go through to the keeper.
On the shorter side again and on middle, Paine pulls it nicely but to the man in front of square.
Back of a length and around off, Paine pushes it to point.

IN THE AIR... CATCH MISSED! FOUR! Oh dear... could that have been taken? Short and wide outside off, Head throws his bat at it. The ball flies towards point where Mitchell Santner is perhaps a touch late in going for the catch with his left hand. The ball whizzes past.
Down the leg side, flick shot missed.
Around off, solidly defended.

Lovely ball, but wonderful shot. Boult gets this really full and makes it to swing back in from outside off. Paine flicks it with the swing, past mid on. Colin de Grandhomme gives it a chase but Mitchell Santner gets to it from deep mid-wicket. Three runs taken.
FOUR! PRISTINE! Full and outside off, Paine reaches out and drives it through the covers. No soul moves! The stand moves to 11 from 16 balls.
A short ball outside off, Paine pushes it towards cover.
A short one and down the leg side, it is pulled down to fine leg for one. Another exciting over comes to an end.

Another snorter! There is half an appeal but nothing! Another short one and around off, it gets big on Paine. He looks to fend at it but the ball whizzes past the outside edge. Snicko confirms there is nothing.
Head is into the 40s! On the pads, it is worked through the legs of the fielder at short leg and a single is taken.
A good short one and well played in the end! It is on the body, Head does well to take one hand off the handle and play it towards short leg.

Brilliant by Boult! Just bowled an over and he putting in so much just to save a run, brilliant from the pacer. Excellent commitment. A short one by Wagner and Paine pulls it this time through square leg. Boult makes a lot of ground to his left and inches before the ropes, he dives and pushes it back in. Saves a run for his side.
A short one again, Paine keeps it out.
Another brute of a bumper! It bounces at a good height. Head hops and tries to fend but the ball hits the higher part of the bat. Luckily it falls onto the ground. End of a testing over by Boult.
Fuller and on middle, Head strokes it to mid on. Probably the first ball off the middle after the wicket of Smith.

Direct hit and it would have been close! On a length and around off, Paine taps it towards point. There is a yes and no situation and the batters eventually go for it. Nicholls from gully gets to the ball and has a shy at the striker's end but misses. HN probably picked the wrong end. Head was in even if that would have hit the stumps. Paine's end is where he needed to go.

Another good delivery! Also, that zipped through. The Kiwis have their tails up at the moment. On a length and around off, it angles away and also takes off a touch. Paine looks to defend but is beaten.

Inside edge but past the leg pole! All of a sudden things have started to happen here. It is on off, Head looks to drive but does so ahead of his body. The ball goes off the inside edge and down to fine leg for one.
Close! This is on off and it comes back in. TH looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Length and on middle, Paine works it to mid-wicket. A successful over for Wagner.
BEATEN! Paine was late in the shot there. It is a low full toss outside off, Paine may have been expecting a bumper. He is late on the drive and is beaten.
The skipper Tim Paine comes out to bat now. That first hour, which did not see much good bowling from the Kiwis, might just help them. 284/5 - bang bang - 300/7?

OUT! In the air... and that is an excellent catch by Henry Nicholls! Wagner who had been troubling Smith throughout has got him finally. Another brute of a delivery by him. Short and on middle, it gets big on Smith who looks to fend at it. It hits the handle, then the glove and lobs towards gully. Nicholls takes a few steps back, times his jump to perfection, stretches one hand upwards and takes it nicely. Wagner is pumped up. Smith's long, long innings comes to an end and he falls 15 short of a ton. Half the side back in the hut for the Aussies. New Zealand now have a chance to keep Australia in  check.
Another one on off, Smith keeps it out nicely.
One more short one and on the body, Smith ducks under it.
Continues bowling it short but this one is down the leg side. It is not played at.

DRINKS BREAK. Not a great hour for the Kiwis. Their bowling is slowly going awry. The pitch is starting to get slower and lower and we might have got to the stage where the frustration might be setting into the bowlers. They have conceded just 27 runs in this hour in 14 overs but that does not really mean the bowling has been terrific.

An appeal but nothing from the umpire! This lands just outside off, it jags back in. Head looks to keep it out but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Boult makes an appeal but the umpire shakes his head.
One more delivery is played with the angle by Smith through mid-wicket. This is wide of the fielder and hence a single is taken.
Smith works it with the angle to the man at mid-wicket.
What happened? Boooooo goes the crowd. Boult comes charging in but Smith backs away. He then indicates sightscreen disturbance.
One more ball outside off, the batter shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, the batter does not fiddle with it.
On a good length and around off, Smith stays back and keeps it out.
On the body again, Travis Head works it to leg gully.
Good fielding! On the shorter side and on the body, Head works it to the left of short leg. Latham dives and makes a good stop.
On the fuller side now, Head is committed to the back foot but does well to play this one out.
One more good bumper, this one skids through. Head though ducks under it with no control of his bat. Also, it was pointing upwards, not the right way to duck.
On the pads, Travis Head works it fine on the leg side and the batters take two.
On the shorter side, Head nudges it on the leg side.
Good shot but for no runs! Slightly ahead of a length and around off, Smith strokes it on the up but finds the cover fielder.
Wide outside off, Smith does not play at that.
Another one on off, Smith stays back and keeps it out.
On a length and it is on the stumps, shapes away a touch. Head looks to defend but it goes off the outer half through point for one.
FOUR! Slapped! A boundary off the bat after 71 balls. A poor delivery this, it is short and outside off. Travis Head slaps it through covers for a boundary.
Fuller and on off, it is driven to mid off.
Trent Boult returns. 23-2-66-1 so far. Change of ends for him. Meanwhile, Wagner is rushing off the field. We suspect it might be for a bathroom break.

That almost fell on the stumps! A nasty bumper this. It is quick and on the body, Smith does not have time to move out of the way. He cops a blow on his chest, it then gets stuck between his body and his hand. He realizes it late, tries to clasp the cheery but then lets it go. It falls beside the stumps! Shouldn't that be handled the ball? Close call that. Reckon no one realized it.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
This bumper seemed slightly quicker, it is well-directed again. Smith evades it nicely.
A short one and on the body, Smith ducks under it.
Back of a length and on off, blocked.
Wagner bangs it short from around the wicket, Head works it wide of short leg and down towards fine leg for one.
Fuller and on middle, Smith strokes it to mid off. Just the wide from the over.
A bumper and on middle, Smith sways out of the way.
On the fuller side around middle, Smith mistimes his shot to mid off.
A yorker this time and on middle, it is jammed out.
On the fuller side around middle, Smith keeps it out.
Another delivery outside off, not very wide this time. Smith lets it be.
Way too wide outside off, Smith lets it be. It has been wided.
A good length ball, around middle, blocked down the pitch.
Around off, watchfully defended.
Around middle, Smith tucks it through square leg for a single.
Full and down the leg side, flicked straight to leg gully.
Down the leg side, left alone.
A short ball outside off, Smith gets across and looks to push but suddenly the ball rises. He manages to fend it towards point.
Another full one, Head finds the man at wide mid off as he drives.
Back of a length and on off, Head pushes it to mid off.
On the fuller side and it tails back in a long way. Head strokes it to mid on.
On the pads, Smith works it through square leg and gets to the other end.
Another length delivery and on off, SS is solid in defense.
On the fuller side and on off, Smith strokes it to mid off.
One more short ball, Head pushes it to mid on. 6 short balls in Wagner's first.
A rib-tickler now, the southpaw nudges it towards short leg.
One more short one but down the leg side, Head does not play at it.
On the off pole, TH stays back and keeps it out.
Down the leg side, Travis looks to flick but misses.
A short one to begin, it is on the body. Head ducks under it.
Neil Wagner is on now!
Close! Southee bowls it around leg. Smith looks to pad it away but fails to do so. The ball goes close past the leg pole.
Back of a length and on off, Smith stays back and keeps it out.
That is lovely bowling! He comes from around the wicket, he lands it on off and then gets it to move away further. Smith looks to defend but gets beaten.
Down the leg side, left alone.

A comfortable three! Excellent pull shot. A short one around off, Head gets on top of the bounce and pulls it through square leg. Boult from fine leg runs across and stops it before it crosses the ropes. Three taken.
On the fuller side outside off, it tails back in a little. Head strokes it to mid on.
Ohhh! Smith was caught in two minds there! Shorter in length and outside off, Smith looks to push it at first but then bails out of the shot.
A short one on the body, Smith ducks under it.
Good length and on off, Smith goes back and keeps it out.
On the pads, Head misses out as he fails to flick it. The ball hits the pad and rolls on the leg side. A leg bye is taken.
Boult angles this into the pads, it seemed like Smith initially looked to flick but then plays it with a straight bat towards cover for one.
Boult goes around the wicket to the right-hander, he lands it on a length. Smith keeps it out.
Well fielded! Fuller and on off, Head creams it back towards the bowler. Southee sticks his right hand out and goes low again and the ball stays in.
Bowls from around the wicket to the left-hander but it is outside off, left alone.
A little too straight, Smith works it down to fine leg and gets to the other end.
On middle, kept out.
A bumper on middle, Smith ducks under it.

NOT OUT! Head got his bat down in time! It would have been a very unfortunate way to get out. Southee goes full and on middle, Smith hits it back towards Tim who sticks his right hand out. The ball brushes the fingers and hits the stumps at the bowler's end. An appeal and the umpire takes it upstairs. Replays show that Head is in.
The bowler deflects the ball onto the stumps at his end. Is Head short? He seems very relaxed.
A back of a length delivery to end! Head defends it out.

Good punch that! Brings up the 50-run stand, another one for the Aussies in this game. 4TH CONSECUTIVE ONE. They would hope this one ends up being a big stand. A shorter and on middle, Head pushes it through mid on and takes two.
On the shorter side again, Head hops and defends it with ease.
A good bumper and on middle, Head ducks under it.
Well fielded! On the pads, Head works it towards mid-wicket. Latham dives to his left and stops it.
No carry there! Outside off, Head lets it be. It goes on the bounce to Watling.
Ends the over with a slower one, he also drags his length back a little. Defended nicely by Smith. So just like the first over of the day, runs from the first ball and then 5 dots.
Continuous to keep it full, this time the line is around off, Smith strokes it firmly but to mid off.
Another one which is full but down the leg side, Smith lets it be.
Another very full delivery on middle, Smith works it to mid-wicket. A new plan maybe by the Kiwis to go very full and on the stumps to Smith. All the balls he has faced today have been very full.
Very full and on off, Smith strokes it to mid off.

FOUR BYES! That swung a long way after passing the batter. It is down the leg side. Smith looks to flick but misses. It keeps going away. Watling dives to his left but he has no chance and the ball goes to the fine leg fence.
Tim Southee to bowl from the other end.
Drags his length back and bowls it slightly shorter around off, Head guides it to point. So except for the first ball, it was a good first over by Boult.
Goes back to bowling it in the corridor of uncertainty. Head shoulders arms to this one.
Now angles this one into the batter, Head works it to mid-wicket.
Full now and outside off, a little movement away from the batter. Head lets it be.
That is a brute of a delivery! Something which Head was surely not expecting. A bumper and that too it is very well-directed. Head at the very end looks to duck but does so very awkwardly.

Runs straightaway for Smith! Boult starts off with a very full delivery outside off, it is a half volley. Smith just puts bat to ball and hits it through covers. Williamson gives it a chase from wide mid off and at the very end, slides and pushes it back in. Saves a run for his side.

It is time for the action to begin now! The Kiwi players make their way out to the middle. They are followed by Steven Smith and Travis Head who will resume from where they left off on Day 1. Smith will face the first ball on Day 2 and he will be up against Trent Boult. He struck in the first over yesterday, can he do so again? We will find out as he comes running in...

On Boxing Day we witnessed - a jam packed stadium, an amazing atmosphere and an excellent contest between bat and ball. After all that, it is the hosts who hold the edge. They have one batter, Steven Smith, who is nearing another ton and Head who has got off to a decent start. Australia will be hoping the two carry on and set the platform for a big first innings score. The Kiwis on the other hand, aren't that far behind in the game, a couple of wickets early and they are right back into this. They bowled well yesterday but with not a lot of luck, they would hope the story is different today. Stay tuned for what promises to be another exciting day of Test cricket.
... Day 2, Session 1 ...

Now then! On Day 2, New Zealand need a few wickets quickly, the second new ball is relatively new and they would hope to enforce a collapse. Australia on the other hand, will hope for one big partnership and the rest to chip in so that they could get to a good first innings total. Do join us for all the action at 1030 local (2330 GMT, Previous day). Till then, take care and goodbye!

The New Zealand bowling was decent throughout. They did not do a lot wrong but probably did not have a lot of luck on their side. They stuck to their plans, bowled accordingly but could not get the reward. Colin de Grandhomme, who did start off well but came back strongly in the next two sessions, was the pick. Boult and Wagner both had a wicket to their name. Southee did look threatening but nothing in the wickets column for him.

It was all about partnerships for Australia! Except for the first wicket, every other partnership was broken only after adding a stand of over 50. None however went onto become something significant. The Aussie batters too failed to make most of the starts they got. Steven Smith however, seems to be all set for another big one. Australia would hope Head can also make use of this opportunity and both can take the team to a big first innings score.

Australia's day in the end! You have to say that, just the 4 wickets in the whole day after electing to bowl, not what you would have thought when that decision was taken. Also, the last session too was dominated by the hosts. Just the one wicket is what they lost and they managed to add 102 runs with Steven Smith looking solid as a rock and Head playing himself in nicely.
Head negotiates it easily! It is a gentle length delivery around middle, Head stays back and keeps it out. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 1!
Makes him play by bowling it on a length and around off, Head keeps it out easily. Last ball coming up...
Looks to swing it back in from outside off but does not get it to come back enough. Left alone. Need to make the batter play here, last two balls coming up.
Outside off, left alone.

EDGY FOUR! How many times have we seen a boundary down in the third man region? From around the wicket, it lands on middle, it straightens. Head looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge. No third slip in place and the ball races down to the third man fence.
On the fuller side, Smith strokes it wide of mid off for one. The fielder there makes a wild throw to the keeper who fails to collect it but no extra run taken.
A sharp bumper to end but it is outside off, Head lets it be.
Goes fuller this time and outside off, Head lets it go again.
A little bit of width on offer outside off, Head does not fiddle with it.
A short one and on middle, it is evaded.
This is on the pads, the batter looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Head misses out on another boundary there.
FOUR! Short, wide and put away! It is outside off, Head cuts it through point for a boundary. 250 up for Australia.
Outside off, not played at.
This is angled into the pads, Smith gently works it to mid-wicket.
Another one on the off pole, defended.
On off, blocked.
That was played with very soft hands! It is on a length and around off, it shapes away. Smith just looks to put bat to ball. The ball though hits the outside edge but falls short of first slip.
Angled into the pads, Smith keeps it out.
Shorter and on off, Head hops and keeps it out.
Leading edge but safe! This one shapes a touch from middle, Head looks to work it across the line against the movement. He gets a soft leading edge towards mid off.
On off and it shapes away. Head opens the face of the bat and guides it to gully.
On middle, Head stays back and keeps it out.
Outside off, Head looks to leave but there is a little extra bounce. Head awkwardly lets it go in the end.
On the pads, Head works it wide of fine leg and takes two. No swing on offer with the second new ball for both the bowlers.
FOUR! Uppish but safe! Fuller and on off, Smith plays a check on-drive. It goes uppishly but well wide of the fielder at mid on and to the boundary.
Outside off again, not played at.
Another tempter outside off, Smith won't be tempted with Stumps around the corner.
Outside off, Smith won't be playing at that so late in the day.
A yorker on off, Smith is ready for it. He gets his bat down in time and jams it out.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Boult is looking to bowl the magic ball, he starts on leg and he tries to swing it away but there is no movement. Head works it through square leg and two is taken.
Back of a length and on off, Head guides it to gully.
This is angled into the middle pole, Smith works it through square leg for one.
This starts on middle and then swings away further. Smith lets it be. Watling does well to dive to his left and stop it.
One a length and outside off, Smith does not play at it.
Bumper! Smith ducks under it.
Another one outside off, Head makes one more leave.
One more delivery outside off, not played at.
Looks to hit the pads of Head but the left-hander gets his bat down and works it through mid-wicket for two.
Good stop! Shorter in length and outside off, Head cuts it hard but Santner at point dives to his right and stops a boundary.
This is angled in from around the wicket, it is still outside off. Due to the angle though Head hangs his bat out but gets beaten.
Outside off, Head shoulders arms to this one.
On the fuller side, it is defended.
Outside off, not played at.
FOUR! Need not run for those! Too full goes Boult and he pays the price. Smith shows the full face of the bat and creams it down to the long off fence.
Starts on the pads and then swings away further. Left alone.
On off this time, Smith covers the line and blocks it out.
Well left in the end! This is just outside off, Smith shuffles across, he initially thinks of playing as he feels the ball would come back in. He sees it does not and leaves it at the last minute.
Full and miles outside off, let through once again. Wastage of the new cherry.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Tempter. Full and outside off, Travis has a lame push and misses.
More inswing, around off, driven straight to cover this time.

FOUR! PRISTINE! This should give Head some confidence. Around middle, nice swing, but Head gets his bat down in time, meets the swing perfectly and drives this with pristine precision. Back past the bowler. Southee bends to stop but the ball whizzes past.
Full and around middle, swinging in, watchfully defended.
Tim Southee into the attack again. 16-4-48-0 so far.
Wide outside off, not played at.
Another ball outside off, Smith does not play at it.
Back of a length and on off, Head looks to defend but due to the outward movement, it goes off the outer half towards point for one.
Down the leg side, Head looks to flick but misses.
Another full delivery, shaping away from middle. Head strokes it back to the bowler.
Some swing for Boult! He bowls it fuller outside off, it is left alone.
The new ball is now available! It has been taken immediately and Trent Boult is back on.
Tosses it up on middle, Smith prods forward and defends.
On off, kept out.
The batsman has been struck on the pads as he looked to play that off the front foot.
Too short and outside off, it is slapped through covers for three.

BEATEN! Turn and bounce! Wow! SAw that for the first time in the game. This lands on off and then spins away sharply, there is also extra bounce. Smith is squared up as he tries to defend, the ball whizzes past the outside edge. The keeper fails to take it and the batters run one bye.
Very full and on middle, this is hit down towards long on for one.
Mitchell Santner is back into the attack!
Head this time gets on top of the bounce and works it wide of the leg gully fielder for one.
On the shorter side around off, Head hops and pushes it to covers.
Nicely bowled! A slower one around off, Head strokes it to mid off.
On the pads again, Head flicks it to the man at mid-wicket.
One more short one on the body, Head works it to mid-wicket.
A short one on the body, Head looks to flick but misses. That nearly kissed the glove on its way.
Outside off, not played at.
Outside off, not played at.
On the fuller side around off, Smith strokes it to cover-point.
On the pads, this is worked towards fine leg for one.
Fuller and outside off, Head looks to go at it a little too hard. It goes off the inner half back to the bowler.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads. One run added to the total.
Full and around middle, swinging in slightly, worked dangerously, across the line, towards mid on. He misses that, he is a goner.
Quick running. A length ball, on the pads, Steven tucks it through square leg and takes a single.
One more short ball, way down the leg side, a bit high as well, left alone.
A short ball, right at the rib cage, SS shoulders arms and gets tickled around the arm pits.
A short ball, outside off, Steven rises with the bounce and plays it towards point.
Full and around middle and leg, worked to the leg side.
Closer to the off pole this time, Head initially thinks of playing at it but then lets it be. Good ball and good leave in the end.
Continues to bowl outside off, Head continues to leave those deliveries.
Third leave in a row as another one is bowled outside off.
One more ball outside off, Head leaves it alone again.
Outside off, Head does not fiddle with it.
This is angled into the pads, Smith shuffles across and works it through square leg for one.
Way down the leg side again, let through.
Way down the leg side, left alone.
Slower ball, fuller in length, around middle, Smith works it through mid-wicket but Tom Latham at short mid-wicket dives to his left and makes a stunning stop.
A bouncer outside leg, SS ducks.
A short ball, around middle, Steven swivels and pulls it, with total control, keeping the ball all along the ground, straight to leg gully.
A length ball around middle, angling away, Smith gets across and defends.
Length and just outside off, Head makes another leave.
One more ball very wide outside off, not sure Head would go after those so early in his innings.
Outside off agian, left alone.
A very wide ball to begin with! Left alone. It has been wided.
Travis Head walks in at number 6, replacing Wade.

OUT! TAKEN! Wade's luck runs out this time! The edge is taken, it carries and the catch is completed. Two for Colin de Grandhomme and he once again provides the breakthrough for the visitors. End of Wade's scratchy innings. Colin bowls one full ball outside off, Wade looks to drive but gets an outside edge straight to Watling who makes no mistake. A wicket right after Drinks. Can New Zealand turn the tide in their favor in the final phase of today's play?

INSIDE EDGE, FOUR! Wade continues to ride his luck! A short one outside off, Wade looks to punch it through the off side away from the body. He gets an inside edge which goes close past the leg pole and down towards the fine leg fence. Wagner there runs towards the ball, dives and tries to push it back in but fails to do so.
Outside off, not played at.

Trent Boult is giving an interview to the spider cam. He says that he is waiting for the second new ball. Hopes that it does work wonders for his side. On Australia not quite running away, Boult says that the team is aiming for basic discipline and not allow easy runs. On the pitch, Trent agrees that it is a very slow deck.

DRINKS! Australia are going along really well at the moment! Smith now looks at his best, Wade on the other hand is struggling but doing well. New Zealand really need a few quick wickets before the end of the day or they will be well behind the game. An important final phase of play awaits.
One more short delivery, Smith again sits under it.
Smith continues receiving short balls! Smith ducks under it.
This is nicely timed! Fuller and around off, Wade creams it through covers and takes three.

FOUR! Another risky shot and Wade once again gets away with it! A short one angled into the body, Wade looks to guide it down to third man but the ball gets big on him. It goes off the top edge over Ross Taylor at first slip and into the third man fence.
A short one on the body, Wade ducks under it.
More runs! Fuller and tailing back in on middle, Smith works it through mid-wicket. Mid on gives it a chase and three is taken.
This time he lets the ball outside off go to the keeper.

Just short! Wade has all the slice of luck at the moment! Colin goes fuller and outside off, Wade goes after it. The ball finally finds the outside edge of the bat but lands just short of the fielder at first slip.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Takes a few steps down the track again, this is bowled outside off, Wade guides it to point.
Bowls another one way too wide outside off, Wade lets it be.
Another one which goes past the outside edge! It is fuller and around off, Wade looks to drive but does so inside the line and gets beaten.
Much better length, fractionally short of full, Steven gets a long way across and defends.
Floated up again, driven straight to cover.
On middle, pushed towards mid on.
Outside off, a bit of flight, driven straight to cover.
Full and outside off, Steven lunges and defends.
A low full toss, around middle, pushed through mid on for a single.
Wade takes a few steps ahead to negotiate the swing. He pushes it towards mid off and takes off for a quick single. Completes it.
Outside off, not played at.
On the fuller side, Wade strokes it to covers.
BEATEN! Just outside off and it is on a length. Wade plays inside the line and gets beaten.
On a length and around off, Wade pushes it to covers.
That came back in a long way! This starts way outside off and then comes back in a long way. Wade leaves it along and the ball goes close past the off pole.
Darts it on off, Smith stays back and pushes it to covers,
Quicker and outside off, Wade opens the face of the bat and guides it through point for one. 200 up for Australia.
On the pads, it is worked to square leg.
Good use of the feet! Gets to the pitch of it and strokes it through covers. Takes three.
On middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Very short and on middle, Smith pulls it towards deep square leg for one. Santner has not been at his best here. Bowled quite a few bad deliveries.
Mitchell Santner is back!
On middle, this is worked through square leg for one.
Shorter and on off, Smith pushes it to mid off.
Way too wide outside off to make the batter play.
On the pads again, Smith works it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, not played at.
Shorter in length and outside off, Wade slaps it through covers, it is not right off the middle. Williamson from wide mid off, hares after it and the batters take three.
On middle, Smith pushes it to mid on.
On the pads, Smith looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Smith now moves out of the way at the very end! He straightaway says sorry.

Beauty! And Wade somehow plays it well in the end! A yorker, it starts on off and tails back in late. Wade gets his bat down in time by taking his front leg out of the way. He is down on the ground but senses it is wide of the fielder at mid on, gets back on his feet and takes one.
On the pads, Wade works it nicely wide of the fielder at fine leg. Calls for two and gets two.
Way too wide outside off to make the batter play.
Back of a length and on off, Wade is solid in defense.
On middle, Smith gets his bat down in time and keeps it out.
On the pads, Wade nudges it down to fine leg and takes one.
Too short on off, Smith works it through square leg and takes one.
On off, Smith taps it on the off side. The batters do think about a run but then do not go for it.
Fuller in length and around off, shapes away. Smith leaves it alone.
This is angled into the pads, it is worked through the leg side for one more run.
Colin de Grandhomme is back into the attack! 14-4-32-1 so far.
Back of a length and on off, Smith stays back and keeps it out.
Third leave in a row as this is once again bowled outside off.
One more ball outside off, not played at.
ABK - 'Guys, why don't you declare...'
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.

FOUR LEG BYES! That was pretty close! This is lands around middle and then comes back in. Smith shuffles right across and looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads. It goes past the keeper and down to the fine leg fence. Boult needed to be a little fuller there.
Starts off with a delivery outside off, Smith would leave those all day long.
Trent Boult is back on! 13-1-43-1 his figures so far.
Shorter and on off, Wade stands tall and defends it onto the ground.
On the fuller side, Wade strokes it to covers. MW is unable to time the ball really well at the moment. Needs that one shot which gets him going.
Outside off, left alone.
BEATEN! Wade on the other hand seems to be struggling. He gets a full ball outside off, Wade goes after it but is beaten.
Like that! Easily rocks back, gets on top of the bounce and pulls the short one towards fine leg for one. 36 is the stand between the two.
On the fuller side, Smith works it to mid-wicket. Smith looks at ease now, comfortably playing the full balls and also the short balls.
One more short one to end! Wade sits underneath it. Maiden.
Fuller and on off, Wade pushes it to covers.
A short one and on middle, Wade ducks under it.
This time angles it into the batter, Wade stays back and keeps it out.
Drags his length back and the line is outside off, left alone.
Fuller in length and it tails away a touch. Wade plays a nice drive but straight to mid off.
Goes full this time after a few short ones. Smith is up for the challenge though as he jams it out.
One more short one on the body, evaded.
Shorter and outside off, Smith pushes it towards cover.
On the shorter side again, Smith moves out of the way.
Another short one on the body, Smith works it to square leg.
A short one from around the wicket to Smith. He mistimes his pull towards leg gully.
The concussion test is going on. Wade looks fine as of now.

FOUR LEG BYES! OFF THE HELMET! Thankfully, Wade is okay. A short ball, on middle, Matthew ducks but takes his eyes off the ball. It shoots off the deck, hits the back portion of the helmet, just above the neck and flies over the keeper to the fine leg fence. Wagner immediately shows concern but Wade shows that he is okay.
A bouncer, around middle, Wade ducks.
A length ball, around middle, MW looks to flick but the ball goes off his pads past short leg. Wade sets off for a single but then changes his mind as he sees leg gully get across.
Full and around off, driven straight back to the bowler.
This one comes back in, but Matthew trusts his judgement and shoulders arms.
Full and outside off, swinging away, left alone.
A single to end! On off, Wade drops it on the off side and takes one.
Back of a length and on off, blocked.
Good shot! Fuller and on off, Wade strokes it back past the bowler. Mid off gives it a chase and keeps it down to two.
On off, Wade guides it to point.

Finds the edge this time as Wade is squared up as he tries to defend. It goes between the second slip and the gully fielder towards third man for two. All these edges though are going along the ground. Probably Wade is playing with soft hands or the wicket does not have a lot of carry.
Lovely stuff! Southee, from the around the wicket angle, gets it to straighten after pitching it on off. Wade lunges to defend but is beaten.
Shorter and on off, Smith keeps it out nicely.
A short one on the body of Smith. He moves out of the way.
Misfield and a run! A slower one outside off, Wade strokes it nicely towards wide mid off. Williamson misfields and a single is taken.
A good short one again, Wade ducks under it again.
Just short! On the pads of Wade. He works it uppishly but just short of Southee at leg gully. Wade would have had his heart in his mouth for a second.
Outside off, not played at.
A lovely shot for no runs! Fuller and on middle, Smith strokes it to mid on.
Southee looks to angle this into the off pole from wide of the crease. Does not angle it in enough and Smith makes one more leave.

FOUR! Streaky again! Smith was completely squared up there! Length and on off, it straightens. Smith is squared up as he tries to keep it out. It goes off the outside edge and through the slip cordon for a boundary. It went all along the ground so even if there had been a third slip, it would not have carried.
One more ball outside off, Smith does not fiddle with it.
Full and wide outside off, Smith leaves it alone.
Good length and on off, Smith keeps it out.
On the shorter side again, Wade nudges it to the man at leg gully. A steamy over from Wagner comes to an end.
Back of a length and on off, Wade stays back and keeps it out.
Shorter and on the body, this is worked to mid-wicket.
A sharp bumper, Wade ducks under it just in time.
On the pads, it is worked down to fine leg for one.
Short and outside off, Smith leaves it alone.
Neil Wagner to bowl from the other end.

Fifty for Smith! He just loves batting on Boxing Day and at the MCG. Did not start off all that well but now seems to got into his own. He gets there by pushing it towards mid off and taking a quick run. End of a good first over after the break for Australia.
Outside off, not played at.

EDGY FOUR! This is fuller and around off, shapes away again. Smith's feet are rooted to the crease, he plays ahead of his body. The ball goes off the edge, all along the ground to the third man fence.

FOUR! Lovely shot! A boundary to score the first runs in this session! Fuller and on middle, Smith strokes it back past the diving mid on fielder for a boundary. An on-drive against a bowler that is swinging the ball away, brilliant.
One more delivery outside off, Smith does not fiddle with it.
On a length and just outside off, Smith initially looks to play but then seeing the away movement, he lets it be.

We are all set for the last session of today! 35 overs left so we are in for a long session. Matthew Wade and Steven Smith will continue their innings. Tim Southee to start proceedings after the break. Here we go...
... Day 1, Session 3 ...

The Kiwi bowling has now started to look a little flat but they will also be looking at the other side of the coin. Australia's middle order is pretty vulnerable and the Black Caps would be aiming to burst through the door. Join us back at 3.30 pm local (0430 GMT). 35 overs left in the day.

88/1 in 29 overs in this session. Australia have managed to see off that nervous passage in the opening session and are reaping dividends. The 83-run stand between Smith and Labuschagne pretty much stamped the authority of the fact that the pitch is slow, which means that the moment the ball stops to swing, the batsmen will find it easy to score.

Steven Smith is up for a chat with Kate Loughnan. On the pitch, he says that it has stayed good for most parts. Observes that a few balls are shooting off a good length, meaning inconsistent bounce but on a whole, it has been good. On his heated discussion with Nigel Llong before Lunch, Steven says that it was not a discussion, just a clarification of thoughts but asserts that he has moved on from that.
A bumper to end the session! Wade ducks under it. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1!

EDGED AND FOUR! That went between the keeper and widish first slip! Wagner can't believe it. He lands this around off and gets it to jag back in. Wade looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. It goes uppishly between first slip and the keeper. Both fail to react and it goes down to the third man fence. The keeper could have probably gone for it, Taylor is a little too wide.
OHHH! This one comes back in from outside off but not enough to make the batter play.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
That must have hurt! Wade shows no pain though. A short one and Wade has not time to move out of the way. He looks to leave it but is hit on the chest.
Back of a length and on middle, Wade keeps it out.
A yorker to end! Smith jams it out.
Gives it air and lands it around off, Smith guides it to cover-point.
On middle, Smith is solid in defense.
On the shorter side and outside off, Wade guides it through point for one.
Outside off, not played at.
Flatter and shorter on off, Smith works it through mid-wicket for one. 150 up for Australia.
Mitchell Santner is back! He is brought on as New Zealand maybe want Wagner to bowl one more before the break.
A delivery down the leg side to end! Wade looks to flick but misses.
One more short one, Wade picks this one late but ducks under it in time.
A short one and on the body of the batter, Wade ducks under it.
Outside off now, it is not played at.
Bowls a length delivery this time around off, Wade solidly keeps it out.
A short one but down the leg side, Wade lets it go to the keeper.

This is interesting. Neil Wagner has not even looked up at his captain. He has charged up to the umpire and handed over his cap. He wants to bowl to Matthew Wade. This should be fun. A leg gully and a short leg in place.
Wide outside off, gentle outswinger, let through.
A touch down the leg side, Matthew tucks it towards fine leg for a run.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
A bit too straight, Smith gets across and tucks it towards fine leg for a single. Moves to 40.
Miles outside off, swinging away, left alone.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Just outside off, Wade leaves it nicely.
On middle, Smith works it through mid-wicket for an easy single.
Another fullish ball and it comes back in from outside off. Smith works it to mid-wicket.
Goes full and on middle, looking to hit the pads of Wade. He gets his bat down and works it towards fine leg for one. Wade is off the mark.
This one starts on off and it comes back in. Smith works it towards deep square leg for one.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Outside off, not played at.
Matthew Wade walks in at his home ground, with 17 minutes to go to Tea.

OUT! BOWLED 'EM! The ploy to continue with Colin de Grandhomme has paid off. He proves to be the partnership breaker. We saw a wicket fall 15 minutes before Lunch and now a wicket 18 minutes before Tea. Labuschagne is disgusted as he walks back. New Zealand though rejoice. This is on a length and around off, this one comes back in sharply and there is also some extra bounce. Marnus looks to leave it alone but the ball hits the elbow and then hits the stumps behind. Marnus can't just believe what has happened. He has been leaving the ball so well but falls in that manner. A good innings by him comes to an end though. New Zealand are into the fragile middle order of the Aussies now. They will hope that this wicket opens the floodgates for them.
A leave as this is bowled outside off.
On off, ML stays back and blocks it.
Well bowled! This starts on off and then shapes away a touch. Marnus looks to defend but it goes off the outer half towards point.
Just outside off, not played at.
Goes full again and on middle, Smith strokes it right off the middle but to mid off.
Another delivery outside off, not played at.
Way too wide outside off, left alone.
On off, Smith stays back and keeps it out.
FOUR! Nailed the pull shot! Short and on middle, Smith rocks back, swivels, gets on top of the bounce and pulls it through square leg for a boundary.
Some shape into the batter but the line is very straight. Labuschagne looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads. It rolls on the leg side. A leg bye is taken.
Back of a length and on off, Smith is solid in defense.
On off, defended.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
WHAT A STAT - In Smith on air informs us that Marnus Labuschagne has got an outside edge 29 TIMES in his short Test career. He has got out only 4 TIMES.
Close! Colin bowls this fuller and on middle, Smith looks to drive but it goes off the inner half, uppihsly but wide of short mid-wicket and short of mid on.
Down the leg side, Smith looks to flick but misses.
On middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Down the leg side to end the over, Marnus looks to flick but misses.
Shorter but closer to the off pole this time, Labuschagne keeps it out.
FOUR! Nicely played! On the shorter side and outside off, Labuschagne lets the ball come to him and then plays it late through point for a boundary.
Fuller and on off, Smith strokes it to mid off and takes off. Williamson there picks the ball up and throws it at the striker's end but misses. ML was well in though.
Goes back to attacking the stumps and it is on a length. Defended.
Full and outside off, Smith opens the face of the bat, uses the pace of the bowler and strokes it square on the off side for two.
Another one well outside off, let through once again.
Well outside off, left alone.

Appeal for LBW, but turned down. A length ball outside off, Marnus gets across and shoulders arms. The ball comes in and hits him high on the thighs. Ball Tracker confirms it to be going over the top.
Full on middle, Marnus works this uppishly, beyond control, but wide of mid on for a couple.
De Grandhomme comes charging in but Labuschagne backs away at the last moment.

EDGED, FOUR! More luck for Marnus Labuschagne. Full and outside off, Labuschagne looks to flick but gets a thick outside edge which flies past first slip to the third man fence. Even if there was a second slip present, don't think it would have carried.
Full and around off, Smith looks to work this to the on side but the ball moves away and squares him up. The leading edge goes through point and a single is taken.
Outside off, left alone.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Full and on middle, ML strokes it back towards the bowler who makes a good one-handed stop.

FOUR! Fifty for Marnus Labuschagne! He gets there in a streaky manner but he won't care. His golden run continues. It has been a knock full of patience and he will be eyeing another ton here. Boult bowls one outside off, Marnus throws his bat at it. It goes off the outside edge between second slip and gully and down to the third man fence.

A huge, huge shout but the umpire shakes his head! This starts on middle and then tails back in. Labuschagne looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit over the knee roll. A huge shout but not given.
