Works this with the angle now towards mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! This is right off the middle! Errs in line and bowls it on the pads, Nicholls flicks it fine on the leg side and a boundary results.

NO BALL AND FOUR! Has that hit the stumps now? It would not have mattered though and yes, it has kissed the leg pole. How did the bails not come off there? It is a big no ball from Starc. He bowls it fuller and around off, it swings back in. Nicholls plays outside the line. It goes off the inside edge, kisses the leg pole and down to the fine leg fence. Nicholls starts to walk back, as he assumed he is bowled in hearing the noise. Then, he sees the bails on the stumps and later, understands that it is a no ball as well.
On off, Blundell works it with the turn to short leg. Two maidens in a row for Lyon.
Blundell uses his feet and then works it with the turn to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball on off, Tom is solid in defense.
Floated up on off, Blundell lunges and keeps it out.
Flatter and on off, defended.
Tosses it up and lands it on off, blocked.
A sharp bumper now, Nicholls spots it late and evades it at the very end.
Down the leg side, Nicholls looks to flick but misses.
Slightly fuller and on off, HN keeps it out solidly.
Shorter and on middle, Nicholls stays back and keeps it out.
Back of a length and around off, it is guided to point.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Mitchell Starc is back! So a double change by the Aussies. 6-2-16-0 so far.
On the stumps, it is worked to short leg. A maiden to begin with by Lyon but he was a little too short in this over.
Shorter in length and outside off, Blundell keeps it out.
Quicker and on off, Blundell goes back and keeps it out.
Outside off, not played at.
A little bit of turn! It lands outside off, it is shorter in length. Turns back in. Blundell has enough time to go back and work it to short leg.
Tosses it up outside off, Blundell lets it be.
Spin for the first time in this innings! Nathan Lyon is on.
A bumper to end! Nicholls watches it go to the keeper.
Shortish and on the body, Nicholls works it to square leg. This delivery was bowled at 147 KPH.
FOUR! Lovely timing! On the pads, Nicholls flicks it nicely over the square leg fielder. It is timed nicely and it goes to the fence.
Fuller and on middle, Nicholls works it to mid on. Cummins is trying to get Nicholls in a similar manner he did in the first innings but the batter is not planting his front foot right across.
On the off pole this time, Nicholls keeps it out nicely.
This is angled away from outside off, Nicholls does not play at it.
That stayed low. Outside off, on a length, TB looked to block that from his crease but the ball hit the deck and shot low. Took the bottom edge and went to gully.
Outside off, tapped behind point for a single.

Huge shout for LBW, turned down. That looked close. Tim Paine has walked right down to his bowler and they have a chat. But eventually, they do not review. A length ball outside off, this came in a long way and hit Tom on his pads as he got his bat down late to defend. Ball Tracker shows the ball to be going over the top. Meanwhile, out of the corner of our eyes, the batsmen have sneaked in a leg bye.
Around off, tight line and length, solidly blocked out.
A length ball, around off, pushed towards mid on.
Full and outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, Nicholls drives this uppishly and it lands JUST SHORT of the bowler.
Around off, coming in, Nicholls' bat twists in his hands as he looks to play straight. The ball goes off the inner half towards mid on.

A short ball, around middle, Blundell swivels and looks to pull. He does not quite get it cleanly and hence, calls for two on seeing the ball travel slowly to fine leg. James Pattinson has some distance to cover but the batsmen are happy with the single.
Outside off, left alone.
Very full outside off, watchfully dug out towards gully.
Around middle and leg, tucked through square leg for a single.

Great follow-up from Pattinson. He bowls this full and fast outside off. Blundell looks to drive but sans any feet movement. Is beaten all ends up. Late movement caused the ball to miss the bat by millimeteres. So, so close.

FOUR! BOSH! That is a quality cricketing shot. A short ball outside off, Blundell is ready and wants to take him on. Pulls it powerfully through mid-wicket. Travis Head starts to run to his left, aiming to cut it crossways. But then, he realizes that the ball is travelling a bit too fast. So he starts to run backwards now, aiming to cut the ball sideways at some point. But that point never comes. The ball meets the ropes and so does Head. 50 UP FOR NEW ZEALAND.
Full and wide outside off, let through once more.
Around off, coming in with the angle, pushed towards short mid-wicket.
Landed outside off, left alone.
On a length outside off, extra bounce, Blundell hops and defends.
Fuller and on off, Nicholls drives but to mid off.
A short one and on middle, Nicholls ducks under it.
Back of a length and on off, Nicholls stands tall and keeps it out.
Length this time and on middle, HN keeps it out.
Fuller and aiming for the pads of Nicholls. He gets it out of the way and works it through mid-wicket for two.
Just outside off, HN does not play at those.
Up and over for three! Shorter and on middle, Nicholls goes back and pulls it over square leg. Takes three.
Back of a length and on off, Nicholls looks to defend but it gets big on him. It goes off the splice on the off side.
On more short ball on the body of Nicholls. He nudges it towards square leg.
On the pads, Blundell looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls on the leg side. A leg bye taken.
Back of a length and on off, Blundell plays it late towards gully.
A short one and on the body, Nicholls manages to pull it towards fine leg. Not sure if it was controlled. A run is taken.
On off, defended.
A stifled appeal! That swung a long way. It starts outside off and then comes back in. Blundell looks to flick with the swing but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Outside off again, not played at.
OHHH! That has gone over the off pole. He left that on length. It is slightly shorter and around off, it comes back in. Blundell lets it be. He left that on height.
Way too wide outside off to make the batter play.
On the fuller side, Blundell creams it but to mid off.
Pat Cummins to bowl from the other end. 5-2-12-0 so far.
Pattinson comes from around the wicket and serves this full and around off, Latham strokes it nicely but to wide mid off.
Just outside off, not played at.
On middle, Nicholls hops and works it to square leg.
On the shorter side, Nicholls stays back and keeps it out on the leg side.
Another one on a length and around middle, Blundell works it towards mid-wicket for one.
Good length and on off, Blundell keeps it out.

We are all set for the game to resume! The Aussie players make their way out to the middle. They are followed by the Kiwi batters Tom Blundell and Henry Nicholls who will resume their innings. James Pattinson to start proceedings for the hosts. Here we go...
... Day 4, Session 2 ...

Pattinson does not get to bowl the one he wanted to! The Kiwis will be relieved they are walking off for a much-needed break. Paine however, is seen having a discussion with the umpire as he feels there could have been one more over bowled. Nevertheless, it has been a tremendous session for the Aussies. Three wickets after declaring and that too Williamson, Taylor and Latham - they just could not have asked for anything better. However, the Kiwi openers started off really well, they looked solid and determined. The introduction of Pattinson though changed things as he ran havoc and blew away the top order. All Australia now need is someone to support Pattinson and they and we could have a day off tomorrow. The Kiwis need a big stand, a mammoth effort from the batters to salvage something out of this game. Their first aim will be to go wicketless in the next session. Can they do so? We will have to wait to find out.
A single to end the over! Short and on middle, this is nudged through square leg for one.
Interesting. Pattinson wants Starc to hurry up. 'Mitch, are you looking at the clock?' He wants to bowl one more over.
Shorter in length and around off, Blundell keeps it out.
Down the leg side, Blundell looks to flick but misses.

Nicholls is off the king pair! Starc goes full and around middle, Nicholls strokes it towards the bowler who gets a hand to it. The ball rolls behind the stumps at the non-striker's end. A single is taken.
One more short one, Blundell continues to take it on. He hits it nicely through square leg for one.

Almost another one! A short one and on the body, Blundell looks to pull but is hurried into the shot. It goes off the glove but lands short of backward square leg. That is the plan for TB, they want to get him caught in that area.
Henry Nicholls walks in on a king pair. 6 minutes to go to Lunch.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Yes, they do get another! Pattinson is breathing fire here. He has got three in the two overs he has bowled and three huge wickets - Latham, Williamson and Taylor. Another poor shot by a Kiwi batter. This is short and there no width on offer. Taylor goes after it as he tries to cut it. That shot is just not on. He gets an inside edge and the ball hits the stumps. New Zealand in dire straits now. Australia will be sensing a win today itself now. A double-wicket over comes to an end.
Another one on the pads, it is worked down to fine leg for two. Taylor is off the mark.
Taylor had to hit that! It is full and around middle and off. Taylor flicks it to mid-wicket. Had he missed that, he was a goner.
This is angled into the pads, Taylor works it to mid-wicket.
The best batsman is gone for New Zealand. The next batsman is out there. Ross Taylor comes in with 10 minutes to go to Lunch.

OUT! Umpire's call! It is just about clipping the leg pole. 'Boooo' goes the crowd here as that is a harsh decision. Williamson could consider himself unlucky here. Australia won't care at all though as they have got the big fish for a duck, he slowly trudges back as he knows his team needed a mammoth effort from him. He does not take a review along though. Pattinson gets the opposition's skipper twice now. This lands on middle and then angles into the pads. Williamson looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal and up goes the finger quickly. Kane reviews after a chat with his partner and then goes for the review. Replays roll in and it shows the ball to be clipping the leg pole but only by JUST! Two wickets down now and both for Pattinson. Still some time left before Lunch, can Australia get another?
Kane Williamson has been adjudged LBW! Big moment in the game. Looks to be missing leg to the naked eye. He has taken the review.
OHHH! This is on a length and around off, it straightens after pitching. Williamson looks to defend the original trajectory but is beaten.
Change of ends for James Pattinson now.
Back of a length and on off, Tom guides it to point.
Nicely flicked but to backward square leg. Full and on the pads, it is hit to backward square leg.
One more ball outside off, not played at.
Shortish and outside off, left alone.
Top shot but for no runs! Fuller and around off, Blundell creams it but straight to covers.
BEATEN! Lovely delivery! This lands just outside off and then angles away. Blundell looks to defend but is beaten. The angle almost does him in there.
Mitchell Starc is back! Change of ends for him.
On the fuller side and on middle, Williamson pushes it to mid on.
Williamson gets squared up there! This lands on off and then straightens. Williamson gets opened up as he tries to defend. The ball goes off the outer half towards gully.
A good short one on middle, Williamson sways out of the way nicely.
Just outside off again, left alone again.
Outside off, not played at.
On the pads, it is worked down to fine leg for one.
Good length and on off, Williamson stays back and keeps it out. End of a successful first by Pattinson.
On the fuller side on off, Williamson strokes it to mid off.
Kane Williamson comes out at number 3, in one of his toughest battles. For now, he has to survive 27 minutes.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Latham should be gutted with himself there. Almost a carbon copy of the way he got out in the first innings but this is an even poorer delivery. It is full and wider outside off, Latham goes after it but the ball kisses the outside edge and goes low to the left of Paine who dives and takes it. The bowling change works wonders and Pattinson strikes in his first over itself. However, Latham is the one to be blamed here. He is such a good leaver of the cricket ball, not sure why did he go after this one and not once but in both the innings he has been dismissed on deliveries which should have been left. Maybe this time around he got bogged down by Cummins, he finally sensed an opportunity to score and went after it and paid the price. The budding opening stand has been cut short.

Clipped nicely! Blundell seems a strong player off his pads. Also, really good running that. Blundell clips this through mid-wicket. Mitchell Starc from mid on gives it a chase. Now, the batters complete two when the pacer picks the ball up. They now take one for the throw and complete the third.
Back of a length and on off, Blundell guides it to point.
Just outside off, not played at.
James Pattinson is on now!
The last ball is outside off, it is left alone.
Cummins drags his length back and bowls it short. Latham works it through square leg and takes two.

FOUR! Cracking shot! Absolutely beautiful. A shot which can give you so much of confidence. Full and on middle, Latham plays it with the angle. Does not look to hit it too hard, just uses the pace of the bowler and strokes it through mid on for a boundary.
Back of a length and on middle, Blundell works it wide of mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Once again, slightly shorter, this one is outside off too. Easy leave.
OHHH! Just short of a length and on off, it comes back in sharply. Blundell looks to defend but misses to get hit near the box. Cummins needs to be a touch fuller. Right now, he is slightly shorter.

BEATEN! It seems like Latham hasn't watched his dismissal from the first innings. He fell to a similar shot. A shot which can be avoided. It is full and outside off, shapes away late. Latham goes after it but this time he gets beaten.
Good length and on off, Latham goes back and keeps it out.
FOUR LEG BYES! Very straight and on the pads, Latham looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. It races down to the fine leg fence.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Way too wide outside off, left alone.
Good length and around off, Latham keeps it out.
Wide outside off, left alone.

A mild shout for LBW. Turned down. Height was the issue. A length ball outside off, coming in a long way, Blundell looked to defend but missed, to get hit on the pads. Ball Tracker confirms it to be going over the top.
Landed outside off, a touch wide, let through.
Full and outside off, driven straight to short extra cover.

Brave leave. THIS was not far away from the off stump. Cummins bowls this on a length, in the corridor of uncertainty. Normally, batsmen are confused whether to play or leave balls in this corridor. Blundell chooses the latter. The ball comes in a long way and just about misses off stump!
A length ball outside off, coming in with the angle, left alone.
Goes for the yorker but misses it by a little. TB works it through square leg and keeps strike.

Nicely clipped! On the pads again, Blundell flicks it towards backward square leg. Cummins runs to his left, dives, collects the ball and lobs it to the fielder running to his right from square leg. The two save two runs for their side.

Right on the arm! A leg bye taken by Latham seems in a little pain as he completes the run. A short one and on the body, does not bounce a lot. Hits Latham on the elbow as he ducks. It lobs towards the leg side and one is taken. Latham looks in pain but then does not any sign of it.
Straighter in line this time, gets it to come back in also at 146 KPH. Blundell gets his bat down in time and works it wide of mid on for one.
Just outside off, Blundell does not play at it.
Back of a length and on off, Blundell stays back and keeps it out.
On the fuller side this time, Latham pushes it to mid off. Maiden over by Cummins.
Slightly shorter and on middle, this one jags back in. Latham looks to flick but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
A sharp bumper, it is on the body, Latham ducks under it.
Just outside off, Latham makes a good leave by covering his off pole.
On the off pole, Latham is solid in defense.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length again, Blundell defends it onto the ground.
On the shorter side, Blundell guides it to point.
On a length and around off, Blundell keeps it out nicely.
One more ball on the pads, Latham works it down to fine leg and gets to the other end.
Third appeal in the three overs bowled. None have gone Australia's way. On the pads, Latham looks to flick but misses. It brushes the pads and goes Paine. An appeal but turned down.
On a length and around off, Latham defends it onto the ground.

FOUR! Up and over! Slightly shorter and around off, Blundell picks the length early and pulls it over mid-wicket for a boundary. He played that nicely, transferred his weight quickly onto the back foot and then got on top of the bounce.
Another appeal and not given again! This seems too high. It lands on off and then comes back in. Blundell looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads.

This one zipped through and there was also extra bounce. It is on a length and just outside off, Blundell looks to leave it but there is steep bounce on this one. It hits the elbow of Blundell. That must have hurt. He walks up to his partner, probably for a breather as it must have stung.
And again! A back of a length delivery is played quite easily by Blundell by going on the back foot.
Outside off, left alone. After seeing the first two deliveries by Cummins, it seems like the pitch has slowed down. Cummins is not getting the ball to skid through like he did in the first innings.
On middle, Blundell keeps it out.
Pat Cummins to bowl from the other end.
Another full toss! Blundell works it through square leg and picks up three. 8 from the first over. It could have easily been a wicket in it but it turns out to be a good one for the Kiwis.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! And a few deliveries like this one too! A full toss on the pads, Blundell is off the mark in style as he clips it and the ball races away.

An appeal but the umpire shakes his head! Missing leg probably. Starc though once again gets some nice shape. It starts on middle and then tails back in. Blundell looks to defend but does so outside the line. The ball hits the pad. Tim Paine and Starc do have a discussion but then don't review. Guess what? Ball Tracker just shows three reds. An early let off, one can say for Blundell. Can he make use of this life? This is probably the kind of a let off a batter who is in need of some runs need.
Down the leg side, Blundell looks to flick but misses.

Some swing for Starc first up but well played too! It is fuller and around off, shapes away a touch. Latham just uses the pace, puts bat to ball and strokes it through covers for one. New Zealand and Latham are underway.
